{"id":61457,"date":"2022-05-31T08:44:53","date_gmt":"2022-05-31T13:44:53","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/?p=61457"},"modified":"2024-01-25T16:21:07","modified_gmt":"2024-01-25T21:21:07","slug":"10-diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-for-small-businesses","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/05\/31\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources","title":{"rendered":"11 Diversity, Equity &#038; Inclusion Resources for Small Businesses"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>You already know that diversity, equity, and inclusion (DEI) has come into the spotlight over the past two years, but the Google Trends chart below shows just how drastic this shift is.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-search-trends.png\" alt=\"diversity equity inclusion search trends\" width=\"720\" height=\"494\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-61488\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-search-trends.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-search-trends-480x329.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>From the beginning of 2020 to today, the popularity of this search term has increased 700%. And there&#8217;s no doubt that a good portion of those searches is coming from businesses trying to figure out how to do their part.<\/p>\n<p>So if you&#8217;re one of those businesses, read on to get 11 resources to help you in your DEI efforts. But first, a quick overview on what these terms mean.<\/p>\n<h2>What is diversity, equity &amp; inclusion?<\/h2>\n<p>According to the <a href=\"https:\/\/dei.extension.org\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">eXtension Organizing Committee on Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion<\/a>, diversity is the presence of differences, equity is fair treatment to those different groups, and inclusion is making sure each of those groups actually feels welcome.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-vs-equity-vs-inclusion.png\" alt=\"diversity vs equity vs inclusion\" width=\"720\" height=\"296\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-61460\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-vs-equity-vs-inclusion.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-vs-equity-vs-inclusion-480x197.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>So in the popular party analogy, diversity is having guests of different races, genders, religions, <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/pride-month-marketing\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">sexual orientations<\/a>, ethnicities, nationalities, socioeconomic statuses, languages, (dis)abilities, ages, and political perspectives. Equity is making sure everyone who wants to attend the party can do so\u2014such as by adding a wheelchair ramp. And inclusion is commonly referred to as being asked to dance, but some better definitions have emerged such as choosing the music and being part of the party-planning committee.<\/p>\n<h2>11 helpful DEI resources for small businesses<\/h2>\n<p>Use these resources to incorporate true <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2020\/11\/05\/accessibility-inclusivity-advertising\">accessibility and inclusivity<\/a> into your marketing and business strategy.<\/p>\n<h3>1. Allyens&#8217; testimonials page<\/h3>\n<p>Allyens is an inclusive marketing agency with an inspiring mission to create &#8220;communications that open minds, connect every single identity, and reach people and goals never seen before.&#8221; Its entire website can serve as a resource for you (as well as an excellent example of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/05\/05\/conversational-tone\">conversational copywriting<\/a>), and its case studies page provides specific examples of how DEI and marketing goals can come together to benefit both your business and society.<\/p>\n<p>In addition, its <a href=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/allyensdotcom\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Instagram<\/a> and other social accounts provide excellent tidbits, like so:<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-allyens.png\" alt=\"diversity equity and inclusion resources - allyens' instagram post\" width=\"720\" height=\"721\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-61461\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-allyens.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-allyens-480x481.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>2. LinkedIn\u2019s Inclusive Language for Marketers Pocket Guide<\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/business.linkedin.com\/marketing-solutions\/content-marketing\/inclusive-language-for-marketers-a-pocket-guide\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">LinkedIn\u2019s Inclusive Language for Marketers Pocket Guide<\/a> is an excellent resources to help you incorporate diversity and inclusion into your brand identity and messaging.<\/p>\n<p>The guide covers<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>What inclusive language is and why it matters<\/li>\n<li>Different forms of inclusive language<\/li>\n<li>Tips to stay inclusive with your language<\/li>\n<li>Common exclusionary language and inclusive alternatives<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-linkedin-inclusive-language.png\" alt=\"linkedin's inclusive language pocket guide\" width=\"720\" height=\"740\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-61462\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-linkedin-inclusive-language.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-linkedin-inclusive-language-480x493.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>3. Accessibilitytest.org<\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/accessibilitytest.org\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Accessibilitytest.org<\/a> tool is also on our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/03\/31\/website-graders\">best website graders list<\/a>. Accessibility Test does an accessibility evaluation of your site using the four leading testers: AudioEye, WAVE, axe, and HTML_CodeSniffer. allows you to test both single pages and full sites. You&#8217;ll get an overall score and then specific recommendations surrounding:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Missing alt text for images<\/li>\n<li>Empty headers<\/li>\n<li>Non-descriptive link text<\/li>\n<li>Missing form labels<\/li>\n<li>Low contrast between background and foreground colors<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-accessibility-test.png\" alt=\"diversity equity inclusion resources - accessibility test results\" width=\"720\" height=\"481\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-61463\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-accessibility-test.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-accessibility-test-480x321.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>As an added bonus, accessibility optimizations can also improve your SEO and help you <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2014\/08\/14\/increase-traffic-to-my-website\">drive more traffic to your website<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h3>4. The Ethical Move<\/h3>\n<p>This inspiring organization reminds us that how we sell matters. In an effort to combat manipulative marketing and improve transparency, responsibility, and honesty\u2014it has a pledge and a badge that businesses can obtain to join the movement.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/dei-resources-theethical-move.png\" alt=\"the ethical move pledge\" width=\"600\" height=\"384\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-61464\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/dei-resources-theethical-move.png 600w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/dei-resources-theethical-move-480x307.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>To take the pledge and receive your badge, go to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.theethicalmove.org\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">theethicalmove.org<\/a>. It also has plenty of free resources for nonmembers, and you can follow them on Instagram <a href=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/theethicalmove\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@theethicalmove<\/a> or sign up for their newsletter.<\/p>\n<h3>5. Google\u2019s Inclusive Marketing Toolkit<\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/all-in.withgoogle.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Google\u2019s Inclusive Marketing Toolkit<\/a> is pretty awesome. It has all the standard components like <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/how-to-create-an-inclusive-marketing-strategy\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">how to incorporate inclusivity into your marketing<\/a>, hiring, and company culture, but if you scroll down, there&#8217;s a section that provides facts and stats about a number of marginalized groups. Click on any group and you&#8217;ll get in-depth information about each group as well as considerations, mistakes, language to use, and more.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/google-inclusive-marketing-toolkit.png\" alt=\"google's inclusive marketing toollkit\" width=\"720\" height=\"575\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-61465\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/google-inclusive-marketing-toolkit.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/google-inclusive-marketing-toolkit-480x383.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>You can also find plenty more <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2023\/02\/27\/diversity-inclusion-marketing-statistics\">diversity, equity, and inclusion in marketing statistics here<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h3>6. iMPACT&#8217;s Inclusive Marketing Examples blog post<\/h3>\n<p>iMPACT&#8217;s <a href=\"https:\/\/www.impactplus.com\/blog\/inclusive-marketing-examples\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">inclusive marketing examples<\/a> covers 15 campaigns by top brands that can give you inspiration and ideas for your own campaigns. For example, The White Collection Bridal Boutique in Portishead, England, with its bride mannequin in a wheelchair.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-inclusion-marketing-examples.png\" alt=\"inclusive marketing example\" width=\"400\" height=\"668\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-61466\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-inclusion-marketing-examples.png 400w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-inclusion-marketing-examples-180x300.png 180w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3>7. The Drum\u2019s diversity column<\/h3>\n<p>The drum is a global marketing news site and magazine that also offers content marketing solutions and peer-to-peer learning networks. Its <a href=\"https:\/\/www.thedrum.com\/topics\/diversity\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">diversity column<\/a> features leaders, creatives, and influencers from marginalized communities to raise awareness and identify solutions.<\/p>\n<h3><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-the-drum.png\" alt=\"dei resources - the drum's diversity column homepage\" width=\"600\" height=\"608\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-61467\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-the-drum.png 600w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-the-drum-480x486.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw\" \/><\/h3>\n<p><strong>RELATED:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/04\/14\/tips-for-minority-owned-businesses\">10 Practical &amp; Inspiring Tips for Minority-Owned Businesses<\/a><\/p>\n<h3>8. Berkeley&#8217;s DEI checklist<\/h3>\n<p>This <a href=\"https:\/\/haas.berkeley.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/EGAL_DEIChecklist.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">DEI checklist<\/a>, provided by the University of California Berkeley Haas School of Business is geared for larger organizations but you can pare it down to accommodate your business. It&#8217;s designed to help you identify gaps and inform action when coming up with your own customized DEI plan.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-dei-checklist.png\" alt=\"Berkeley's DEI checklist\" width=\"256\" height=\"330\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-61468\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-dei-checklist.png 400w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources-dei-checklist-233x300.png 233w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 256px) 100vw, 256px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>It&#8217;s separated into the institutional and community level and covers recruitment and hiring, employee evaluation and promotion, pay, flexible work, care and health, accountability, and equity-fluent leadership.<\/p>\n<h3>9. SHRM\u2019s DEI policy template<\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/04\/28\/diversity-in-marketing\">True diversity<\/a>, equity, and inclusion comes from the inside out. The Society for Human Resource Management has a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.shrm.org\/resourcesandtools\/tools-and-samples\/policies\/pages\/diversitypolicy.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">diversity, equity and inclusion policy template\u00a0<\/a>you can use as a starting point for your own. You&#8217;ll want to customize it to your culture, industry, and practices, and as with any policy you create, it should be reviewed by your legal counsel for compliance with applicable laws.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-policy-template.png\" alt=\"DEI policy template\" width=\"720\" height=\"377\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-61469\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-policy-template.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/diversity-equity-inclusion-policy-template-480x251.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>10. The Accessible Social Checklist<\/h3>\n<p>And finally, the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.accessible-social.com\/checklist\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Accessible Social Checklist<\/a> by the free resource hub Accessible Social. The first page has a list of 23 boxes to check, such as:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Suitable contrast in graphics to make sure the copy is legible.<\/li>\n<li>Flattened copy in alt text.<\/li>\n<li>Removing emojis from the middle of words.<\/li>\n<li>Putting multi-word hashtags in Camel Case.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>And the second page has a full glossary of terms to know (like flattened copy and Camel Case).<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/accessible-social-checklist.png\" alt=\"the accessible social checklist screenshot\" width=\"582\" height=\"370\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-61490\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/accessible-social-checklist.png 582w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/accessible-social-checklist-480x305.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 582px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>11. Ben&#8217;s Definitive Guide to Disability Inclusion in the Workplace<\/h3>\n<p>Ben is an all-in-one employee benefits platform that makes it easy for employers and companies to give rewards and benefits to their employees. Its <a href=\"https:\/\/www.thanksben.com\/the-definitive-guide-to-disability-inclusion-in-the-workplace\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Definitive Guide to Disability Inclusion in the Workplace<\/a> is an online experience that provides everything you need to know for improving workplace inclusivity\u2014including stats, definitions, and useful links and resources.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/disability-inclusion-guide.png\" alt=\"screenshot of ben's definitive guide to disability inclusion in the workplace\" width=\"500\" height=\"426\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-63198\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/disability-inclusion-guide.png 500w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/disability-inclusion-guide-480x409.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 500px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h2>Bookmark these diversity, equity &amp; inclusion resources<\/h2>\n<p>While the explosion of DEI awareness is positive, it&#8217;s unfortunate that it has taken society so long\u2014and events as tragic as those that occurred in 2020\u2014for this to happen. Furthermore, greater awareness does not mean greater action. We&#8217;re still very much in a phase where we&#8217;re more aware of how much action needs to be taken. But you can do your part by using these resources to promote and practice diversity, equity, and inclusion in your business and marketing strategies:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Allyens&#8217; testimonials page<\/li>\n<li>LinkedIn\u2019s Inclusive Language for Marketers Pocket Guide<\/li>\n<li>Accessibilitytest.org<\/li>\n<li>The Ethical Move<\/li>\n<li>Google\u2019s Inclusive Marketing Toolkit<\/li>\n<li>iMPACT&#8217;s Inclusive Marketing Examples<\/li>\n<li>The Drum\u2019s diversity column<\/li>\n<li>Berkeley&#8217;s DEI checklist<\/li>\n<li>SHRM\u2019s DEI policy template<\/li>\n<li>The Accessible Social Checklist<\/li>\n<li>Ben&#8217;s Definitive Guide to Disability Inclusion in the Workplace<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>You can also refer to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/04\/30\/email-accessibility\">our post on making your emails accessible<\/a> if email marketing is a part of your strategy.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Incorporate true DEI into your marketing with these free tips, templates, and tools.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":87,"featured_media":61472,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"_et_pb_use_builder":"","_et_pb_old_content":"","_et_gb_content_width":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[104],"tags":[],"dipi_cpt_category